post_text: The Southeastern Indiana YMCA has recently launched a Virtual Kids YMCA on their website, located at https://siymca.org/programs-and-classes/. Each day they are uploading a short newsletter for parents and kids to get some ideas for physical activity and arts/crafts and STEM activities, geared more towards primary, intermediate, and middle school ages, to help during this time of pause. There’s no Y membership needed. Check it out if interested. #weRmilan
